case_address_found_1: Lincoln Park - in the Milwaukee River
case_circumstances: This full term Unidentified White/African American Female infant was found dead on April 26th, 1990 in the Milwaukee River located in Lincoln Park at 5000 North Milwaukee River Parkway in Glendale, WI.  Strangers that were fishing on the edge of the Milwaukee River in Lincoln Park found the fetus when it became snagged on their fishing line that had been cast into the river.  Once the strangers reeled in the fishing line, they discovered that the object being reeled in was a human fetus and called the police.
